Aspirants concerned about lack of fairness and transparency in the JP nominations have started seeking political refuge in PNU, Kanu, DP and Maendeleo Chap Chap.On December 20, a huge PNU delegation from Nyandarua met party leader Peter Munya in Meru. They have now opened an office at 2brothers Plaza near JM Hospital, Ol Kalou. They are set to open more across the county.&ldquo;Although for now we keep our cards close to the chest, we cannot allow ourselves to be shepherded into one outfit where our future is uncertain,&rdquo; former councillor Jimmy Chogi told the Star yesterday.